revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{high use}}

== Usage ==
Add {{tl|reflist hide}} to a page to hide the references list on talk pages, user pages, help pages, etc.. It should not be used in articles. 

Reference error messages are seen in preview, but not after saving.

{{tl|reflist hide}} allows discussion of tables, prose, etc. without having to remove the references from them, and without cluttering up the talk page.

If you want to discuss references, but want them just for a specific talk section, then use {{tl|Reflist-talk}} in that talk section. If you want those to be collapsed use {{tl|Sources-talk}} or this redirect to it: {{tl|Reflist-talk-collapsed}}.

== See also ==
* {{tl|Reflist-talk}}, collects references where it is placed.
* {{tl|Sources-talk}}, a collapsed version of {{tl|Reflist-talk}}
* {{tl|Notelist-talk}}, gathers footnotes added with {{Tl|efn}}

<includeonly>{{sandbox other||
[[Category:Reference list templates]]

}}</includeonly>

